BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, June 27 (XINHUA) -- Chinese Vice-Premier 
and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen left here today for official 
visits to Russia, Belarus, Lithuania and Estonia, at the 
invitation of the foreign ministers of the four countries. 
  At the end of the visits, Qian is scheduled to tour Finland, 
according to Chinese Foreign Ministry officials. 
  He was seen off at the airport by He Chunlin, deputy 
secretary general of the State Council, Tian Zengpei, 
vice-minister of foreign affairs, as well as senior diplomatic 
officials from Russia, Belarus, and Finland. 

